In [30]:
surface_elevation_arr=ds.topo.where(ds.topo>0,0).data
bedrock_topography_arr=ds.topo.data
ice_thickness_arr=ds.topo.data*0
mask_arr=(ds.topo>0).data*1

ds_new = xr.Dataset(
    data_vars=dict(
        surface_elevation=(['lat','lon'], surface_elevation_arr,{'units':'m'}),
        bedrock_topography=(['lat','lon'], bedrock_topography_arr,{'units':'m'}),
        ice_thickness=(['lat','lon'], ice_thickness_arr,{'units':'m'}),
        mask=(['lat','lon'], mask_arr,{'units':'/'}),
    ),
    coords=dict(
        lon=ds.lon-180,
        lat=ds.lat,
    ),
    attrs=dict(description=''),
)

ds_new.to_netcdf('./Eocene/topog_Eocene_Herold2014_climberX.nc')

Emission Scenarios¶

  • reference: Harper et al. 2018 https://doi.org/10.1029/2019PA003699, e.g. 3800 GtC emitted at constant rate over 15,000 years (which is quite moderate, i'd expect not more than 2-3°C warming)
In [31]:
times=np.arange(0,50e3+1,1)
c_emis=np.zeros(times.shape)
c_emis_total=3800. # PgC, Harper 2020
c_emis_length=15e3 #years, Harper 2020
c_emis_rate=c_emis_total/c_emis_length # PgC/yr
c_emis_start=int(5e3) #years
c_emis[c_emis_start:c_emis_start+int(c_emis_length)+1]=c_emis_rate

ds_c_emis = xr.Dataset(
    data_vars=dict(
        co2_emis=(['time'], c_emis,{'units':'PgC/yr'}),
    ),
    coords=dict(
        time=times,
    ),
    attrs=dict(description=''),
)

ds_c_emis.to_netcdf('./Eocene/co2_emis_PETM.nc')

Comparison of Equilibrium State with other Climate Models¶

  • i've requested access to the DeepMIP model output data base, but didn't receive a response yet
  • in the existing DeepMIP publications, maps of absolute surface temperatures and precipitation are missing

Valdes et al. 2021 (HadCM3)¶

In [45]:
valdes_scotese_2_df = pd.read_csv('./Data_fromOthers/ClimateModel_Valdes2021/runs_scotese_2_data.txt', sep=" ", header=None)
valdes_scotese_2_df.columns = ["run", "age", "gmst", "pCO2"]
for ii in valdes_scotese_2_df.index:
    path='./Data_fromOthers/ClimateModel_Valdes2021/data_scotese_2/'+valdes_scotese_2_df.run[ii]
    valdes_scotese_2_df.loc[ii,['path']]=path
    valdes_scotese_2_df.loc[ii,['set']]='scotese_2'
#data

valdes_scotese_spinupa_df = pd.read_csv('./Data_fromOthers/ClimateModel_Valdes2021/runs_scotese_spinupa.txt', sep=" ", header=None)
valdes_scotese_spinupa_df.columns = ["run", "age", "pCO2"]
for ii in valdes_scotese_spinupa_df.index:
    age_str=valdes_scotese_spinupa_df.loc[ii,['age']][0]
    valdes_scotese_spinupa_df.loc[ii,['age']]=int(age_str[:age_str.index('Ma')])
    path='./Data_fromOthers/ClimateModel_Valdes2021/data_scotese_spinupa/'+valdes_scotese_spinupa_df.run[ii]
    valdes_scotese_spinupa_df.loc[ii,['path']]=path
    valdes_scotese_spinupa_df.loc[ii,['set']]='scotese_spinupa'

valdes_scotese_2_sel_df=valdes_scotese_2_df[(valdes_scotese_2_df.age>=50) & (valdes_scotese_2_df.age<=60)]    
valdes_scotese_spinupa_sel_df=valdes_scotese_spinupa_df[(valdes_scotese_spinupa_df.age>=50) & (valdes_scotese_spinupa_df.age<=60)]

valdes_sel_df=pd.concat([valdes_scotese_2_sel_df,valdes_scotese_spinupa_sel_df]).reset_index(drop=True)

Plots Comparison¶

In [37]:
def plot_comp(prc,temp,lo_mask,ax):
        p=prc.plot(ax=ax,transform=ccrs.PlateCarree(), cmap=cmocean.cm.rain,vmin=0,vmax=8,levels=8+1,add_colorbar=False) #
        xr.plot.contour(temp,ax=ax,transform=ccrs.PlateCarree(),levels=[-15,0,15,25,30,40],colors=['w','cyan','b','darkorange','r','magenta'],linewidths=2.5,alpha=0.9);
        p.axes.gridlines(color='black', alpha=0.5, linestyle='--')
        lo_mask.plot.contour(ax=ax,transform=ccrs.PlateCarree(),levels=[0.5],colors='k');
        return p
